  "prompt": "Does NASA recruit Indians?",
  "response": "NASA is an organization that hires individuals based on their qualifications and experience, regardless of nationality. However, the ability for someone from India or any other country to work for NASA may depend on specific visa and immigration regulations, as well as the nature of the position. \n\nFor example, U.S. citizenship or permanent residency is often required for many government positions at NASA. However, there are opportunities for international collaboration and research partnerships where non-U.S. citizens, including Indians, can work with NASA through various programs or contracts, often associated with academic institutions or private sector organizations.\n\nIf you're interested in working with NASA, keeping an eye on their job openings and understanding the requirements for each position is a good approach. Additionally, pursuing relevant educational qualifications in science, technology, engineering, or mathematics (STEM) fields can enhance your eligibility for roles in aerospace and space research.",
